title: St. James Court art show begins Oct. 2

LOUISVILLE, Ky (WHAS11) -- Old Louisville will see thousands of people as the St. James Court Art Show starts this Friday. 
From October 2 through October 4, St. James Court in Old Louisville will be holding an art and crafts show. More than 700 vendors will be there to showcase their various works of art. 
The best part about it? Admission is completely free. 
The fair starts at 10 a.m. Friday and Saturday and will end at 6 p.m. Sunday will also start at 10 a.m. but will end at 5 p.m.  //on.whas11.com/1FLie0A More Stories
